<title>NETHERLANDS: Fortis still has no comment on ScotAm.</title>
<headline>Fortis still has no comment on ScotAm.</headline>
<dateline>UTRECHT, Netherlands 1997-02-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dutch-Belgian financial group Fortis declined to comment on a Financial Times report that it had decided not to bid for Scottish Amicable.</p>
<p>&quot;We are sticking to our earlier position that we do not comment on individual cases and we have nothing to add,&quot; a Fortis spokeswoman said.</p>
<p>Last week newspapers reported that Dutch-Belgian financial services group Fortis was ready to make a bid for Scottish Amicable but Fortis declined to make any comment.</p>
<p>Scottish Amicable has said that Abbey National Plc and insurer Prudential Corp Plc had made offers for Amicable and that it had received expressions of interest from other potential buyers.</p>
<p>Market sources and analysts have mentioned Halifax Building Society, banking group National Westminster Australian Mutual Provident and Dutch firms Aegon, ING and Fortis as possible bidders.</p>
